### Issue 3: Webhook Handshake Fails

**Symptom:** Webhook creation request times out or fails with "handshake failed" error. Webhook doesn't become active.

**Cause:** Your endpoint didn't respond to the handshake request within the timeout period (typically 10 seconds), didn't include the X-Hook-Secret header in the response, or returned the wrong secret value.

**Solution:**
```javascript
// âœ… Correct webhook handshake implementation
app.post('/webhooks/asana', (req, res) => {
  const hookSecret = req.headers['x-hook-secret'];

  // MUST respond to handshake FIRST before any async operations
  if (hookSecret) {
    console.log('Webhook handshake received');

    // Set the header BEFORE sending response
    res.setHeader('X-Hook-Secret', hookSecret);

    // Send 200 OK response immediately
    res.status(200).send();

    // AFTER responding, store the secret asynchronously
    setTimeout(() => {
      storeWebhookSecret(req.body.webhook.gid, hookSecret);
    }, 0);

    return;
  }

  // Handle normal webhook events...
});
```

Common mistakes:
```javascript
// âŒ DON'T: Respond after async operations
if (hookSecret) {
  await storeInDatabase(hookSecret); // Too slow!
  res.setHeader('X-Hook-Secret', hookSecret);
  res.send(); // Timeout!
}

// âŒ DON'T: Forget to set header
if (hookSecret) {
  res.status(200).send(); // Missing X-Hook-Secret header!
}

// âŒ DON'T: Return wrong secret
if (hookSecret) {
  res.setHeader('X-Hook-Secret', 'hardcoded-value'); // Must match received secret!
  res.send();
}
```

**Prevention:** Test webhook endpoints locally using ngrok or similar tunneling service before deploying. Ensure your server responds to handshakes within 2-3 seconds maximum.

**Source:** https://developers.asana.com/docs/webhooks-guide

