### Issue 5: OAuth Token Expiration

**Symptom:** API calls work initially but start failing with 401 Unauthorized errors after ~1 hour. User must reconnect their Asana account.

**Cause:** OAuth access tokens expire after a set period (typically 1 hour). Your app needs to use the refresh token to obtain a new access token before it expires.

**Solution:**
```javascript
/**
 * Auto-refreshing Asana client wrapper
 */
class AsanaClientWithRefresh {
  constructor(tokens, onTokenRefresh) {
    this.tokens = tokens; // { accessToken, refreshToken, expiresAt }
    this.onTokenRefresh = onTokenRefresh; // Callback to save new tokens

    this.client = Asana.ApiClient.instance;
    this.oauth = this.client.authentications['oauth2'];
  }

  /**
   * Ensure token is valid, refresh if needed
   */
  async ensureValidToken() {
    // Check if token expires in next 5 minutes (300000ms buffer)
    const willExpireSoon = Date.now() + 300000 >= this.tokens.expiresAt;

    if (willExpireSoon) {
      console.log('ðŸ”„ Access token expiring soon, refreshing...');
      await this.refreshToken();
    }

    // Set current access token
    this.oauth.accessToken = this.tokens.accessToken;
  }

  /**
   * Refresh access token using refresh token
   */
  async refreshToken() {
    try {
      const response = await this.client.fetchAccessToken({
        client_id: process.env.ASANA_CLIENT_ID,
        client_secret: process.env.ASANA_CLIENT_SECRET,
        refresh_token: this.tokens.refreshToken,
        grant_type: 'refresh_token'
      });

      // Update tokens
      this.tokens = {
        accessToken: response.access_token,
        refreshToken: response.refresh_token || this.tokens.refreshToken,
        expiresAt: Date.now() + (response.expires_in * 1000)
      };

      // Notify app to save new tokens
      if (this.onTokenRefresh) {
        await this.onTokenRefresh(this.tokens);
      }

      console.log('âœ… Token refreshed successfully');

    } catch (error) {
      console.error('âŒ Token refresh failed:', error);
      throw new Error('Failed to refresh token. User must re-authorize.');
    }
  }

  /**
   * Make API call with auto-refresh
   */
  async makeApiCall(apiCall) {
    await this.ensureValidToken();
    return await apiCall();
  }
}

// Usage
const asanaClient = new AsanaClientWithRefresh(
  userTokens,
  async (newTokens) => {
    // Save new tokens to database
    await db.users.update(userId, { asanaTokens: newTokens });
  }
);

// Make API calls - token refresh is automatic
const tasks = await asanaClient.makeApiCall(() => {
  const tasksApi = new Asana.TasksApi();
  return tasksApi.getTasks({ assignee: 'me', workspace: workspaceGid });
});
```

**Prevention:** Always implement token refresh logic when using OAuth. Store expiresAt timestamp and check it before every API call. Use background jobs to proactively refresh tokens before they expire.

**Source:** https://developers.asana.com/docs/oauth

