### Issue 6: Number Custom Field Format Ignored

**Symptom:** When creating a number custom field via the API with a specific format (currency, percentage, etc.), the format is ignored and the field remains unformatted. Updating the format via PUT also doesn't work.

**Cause:** Known API bug where the format field is not properly processed during custom field creation or updates via API.

**Workaround:**
```javascript
// Create number custom field (format will be ignored)
const customFieldsApi = new Asana.CustomFieldsApi();
const field = await customFieldsApi.createCustomField({
  data: {
    name: 'Estimated Cost',
    resource_subtype: 'number',
    workspace: workspaceGid,
    precision: 2,
    format: 'currency' // This will be ignored by API bug
  }
});

console.log('âš ï¸ Custom field created but format may need manual setting');
console.log('Please set format manually in Asana UI: Project Settings > Custom Fields');

// Alternative: Create field via UI first, then fetch its GID for API usage
```

**Prevention:** For critical formatted fields (currency, percentages), create them manually in the Asana UI and fetch their GIDs programmatically. Use text fields with formatting in your app layer as a workaround.

**Source:** https://forum.asana.com/t/when-creating-a-number-custom-field-via-the-api-the-format-field-is-ignored/195450

