### Issue 4: Webhook Events Missing Details

**Symptom:** Webhook events contain only minimal information (resource GID and action type). Full task details are not included.

**Cause:** By design, Asana sends "compact" webhook events to minimize payload size and delivery time. Events are notification triggers, not full data payloads.

**Solution:**
```javascript
// Webhook handler that fetches full details
app.post('/webhooks/asana', async (req, res) => {
  // Respond immediately (required)
  res.status(200).send();

  // Process events asynchronously
  const events = req.body.events || [];

  for (const event of events) {
    console.log(`Event: ${event.action} on ${event.resource.resource_type}`);

    // Event only contains: { resource: { gid, resource_type }, action: 'changed', parent: {...} }
    // Must fetch full details with another API call

    if (event.resource.resource_type === 'task') {
      const tasksApi = new Asana.TasksApi();

      // Fetch full task with specific fields
      const task = await tasksApi.getTask(event.resource.gid, {
        opt_fields: 'name,completed,assignee.name,custom_fields,due_on'
      });

      // Now you have full task details
      console.log('Full task:', task.data);

      // Process the task...
      await processTaskUpdate(task.data);
    }
  }
});
```

**Optimization:** Batch fetch multiple resources if processing many events at once:
```javascript
// If you have 10 task change events, batch fetch them
const taskGids = events
  .filter(e => e.resource.resource_type === 'task')
  .map(e => e.resource.gid);

// Use batch API or Promise.all for parallel fetches
const tasks = await Promise.all(
  taskGids.map(gid => tasksApi.getTask(gid, { opt_fields: 'name,completed' }))
);
```

**Prevention:** Always design webhook handlers to fetch additional details when needed. Cache frequently accessed data like project names and custom field definitions.

**Source:** https://developers.asana.com/docs/webhooks-guide

